  "body": "# data-\\* atributes not updating\n\nI'm using react + redux, I have some input fields with the data-error atribute.\nThe data-error property is used to give feedback to the user if some field is not valid.\n\nThe inital state looks like this:\n\n``` javascript\n{\n  error: {\n    invalidName: false\n  }\n}\n```\n\nthe component looks like this\n\n``` javascript\nconst Component = ({ error, onSubmit }) => {\n  const { invalidName } = error\n  return <form onSubmit={onSubmit}>\n    ...\n    <input type='text' name='fullName' data-error={invalidName} />\n  </form>\n}\n```\n\nand its passed to the component via  `connect`\n\n``` javascript\nconst mapStateToProps = ({ error }) => ({\n  error\n})\n\nconst mapDispatchToProps = (dispatch) => ({\n  ...\n})\n\nexport default connect(\n  mapStateToProps,\n  mapDispatchToProps\n)(Component)\n```\n\nWhen I hit submit a helper validates the data, and if the data is not valid\nthe helper calls a reducer that return something like this\n\n``` javascript\n{\n  ...state,\n  error: {\n    invalidName: true,\n    ...state.error\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI am using Redux Logger and when I inspect the `nextState` I get the desired state,\nbut the `data-error` continues to be `false` instead of `true`\n",
